Task 1 :Basic_Task

1.ls command and enter (screenshot attached below)
ls meaning:this command lists all the files and dirctories.files are written in white and directories in blue.
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ ls

Desktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  Public  Templates  Videos


2.pwd command and enter(screenshot ATTACHED BELOW)
pwd meaning:prints the name of the current or working directory
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ pwd
/home/joyous

3.mkdir workspace the cd workspace(screenshot)
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ mkdir workspace
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~/workspace$ ls

4.ls typed in and then enter(screenshot attached below)
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~/workspace$ ls

5.Make a new file called README.md (you can use the touch command to do this)
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~/workspace$ touch README.md

6.cp README.md CHANGELOG(screen shot attached)
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~/workspace$ cp README.md CHANGELOG.md
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~/workspace$ ls
CHANGELOG.md  README.md

