Task 3: Cat Commands

Working from the /home directory.

# 1:Create 3 files namely umuzi.md, recruits.md and cohort.md.

joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ touch umuzi.md, recruit.md, cohort.md
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ ls
cohort.md  Documents  Music     Public       Templates  Videos
Desktop    Downloads  Pictures  recruit.md,  umuzi.md,  workspace

# 2: manually add content to each file.
# 3: cat *.md          // Displays content in all .md files

joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ cat umuzi.md, recruit.md, cohort.md
umuzi is a great enviroment
i am a new recruit at umuzi, cohort 17.
i am cohort 17 and it is really great to be here.

# 4:  cat umuzi.md, recruit.md, cohort.md > summary.md

joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$  cat umuzi.md, recruit.md, cohort.md > summary.md
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ cat summary.md
umuzi is a great enviroment
i am a new recruit at umuzi, cohort 17.
i am cohort 17 and it is really great to be here.

# 5: echo "The End" >> summary.md

joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ echo "The End" >> summary.md
joyous@joyous-Mecer-X102:~$ cat summary.md
umuzi is a great enviroment
i am a new recruit at umuzi, cohort 17.
i am cohort 17 and it is really great to be here.
The End


